title: Prep Player of the Week: Honorable mention (Oct. 13)
text:
Prep Player of the Week: Honorable mention (Oct. 13) updated Monday, October 12, 2015 - 10:24pm 
CROSS COUNTRY 
Chase Kennedy, Sue Ann Moralis, East Jackson: Kennedy won the boys championship race at the Alexander Invitational in 15 minutes, 32.21 seconds. Moralis finished third (18:03.12) in the girls championship race. 
Thomas Moore, North Oconee: Moore won the boys championship at the Gene Mullin Invitational in 16 minutes, 28.75 seconds. 
Anna Marian Block, Athens Academy: Block won the girls championship race at the Gene Mullin Invitational in 18 minutes, 51.44 seconds. 
FOOTBALL 
Colby Wood, Jefferson: Wood rushed for 153 yards and two touchdowns on 23 carries in Jefferson’s 17-0 win over Morgan County on Friday. 
J.J. Burton, Madison County: Burton scored two rushing touchdowns and hauled in a scoring pass in Madison County’s 59-29 win over Chestatee on Friday. 
Joseph Russell, Athens Christian: Russell scored three rushing touchdowns in a 35-7 win Friday against Towns County. 
Joey Parrillia, Jacob Parker, Bethlehem Christian: Parrillia tallied 215 rushing yards and two rushing touchdowns on 16 carries in a 39-36 win over First Presbyterian Christian on Friday. He also had a receiving touchdown. Parker was 11 of 17 for 175 yards and three touchdowns. 
Jordan Hightower, Kevon Hudson, Prince Avenue Christian: Hightower forced a fumble and picked off two passes, including one he returned 40 yards for a score in Prince Avenue’s 45-14 win Friday over Athens Academy. Hudson scored three rushing touchdowns. 
VOLLEYBALL 
Ansley McClain, Emily Boswell, Oconee County: McClain tallied 55 assists and five aces in the Warriors’ five-set win over Jefferson on Saturday. Boswell recorded 43 digs. 
Abby Wood, Grace Haney, Madison Corbett, Olivia Przybysz, Jefferson: In a win over Morgan County and the region final loss to Oconee County, Wood tallied 38 digs, 22 kills and five aces, Haney snagged 34 assists and six aces, Corbett recorded 42 assists and eight digs and Przybysz finished with 46 digs. 
SOFTBALL 
Jessie Marvin, East Jackson: Marvin recently helped East Jackson beat Elbert County twice to qualify for the state tournament. She struck out 11 batters in the final game to clinch the state tournament bid. 
Kinsley Dickerson, Kiara Barron, Gina Urell, Lexi Veamoi, Athens Christian: Last Friday, Dickerson went 4-for-4 with two runs and Urell and Barron went 3-for-3 in a win over Hebron Christian. Veamoi struck out nine batters and allowed one hit in a four-inning win over Commerce. 
Emmy Soles, Prince Avenue Christian: Soles pitched a complete-game one-hitter with 11 strikeouts in a win over Athens Christian last week. 
— Nicole Saavedra/Staff
